<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>aps-environment</key>
    <string>development</string>
    <!-- Shared container + keychain access group (app groups double as keychain access
         groups on iOS) so the KlicShare extension can read the auth tokens. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
    <array>
        <string>group.com.klic.mobile.app</string>
    </array>
    <!-- Passkeys (§10.4/§13.10): the RP is klic.pstepanov.dev — its AASA serves
         webcredentials for this app id. Universal links (§13.8): applinks for
         /u/* and /add/* friend links.

         The ?mode=developer twins bypass Apple's AASA CDN and fetch the file
         straight from the origin. They only apply to development-signed builds
         and only when the device opts in (Settings → Developer → Associated
         Domains Development); production installs ignore them. Useful when the
         CDN copy is stale or the origin isn't reachable from the CDN.

         The legacy webcredentials:api.89.34.230.2.sslip.io entry is gone: the
         RP migrated to klic.pstepanov.dev, and Apple's CDN 404s the sslip.io
         host anyway, so that entry could never validate on release installs.

         AltStore/AltServer re-signing does NOT preserve this list: the app is
         re-signed with the provisioning profile's entitlements, which carry
         associated-domains = "*" (an authorization wildcard, not a domain), so
         passkeys and universal links break on AltStore installs regardless of
         what is written here. Install the dev-signed IPA directly (Xcode,
         devicectl, Apple Configurator) to keep the domain list intact;
         passkeys degrade with a readable error and universal links simply
         don't open the app (QR scanning still works). -->
    <key>com.apple.developer.associated-domains</key>
    <array>
        <string>webcredentials:klic.pstepanov.dev</string>
        <string>webcredentials:klic.pstepanov.dev?mode=developer</string>
        <string>applinks:klic.pstepanov.dev</string>
        <string>applinks:klic.pstepanov.dev?mode=developer</string>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
